silver_reasoning: since greg is a frog (sentence 3), and julius is also a frog (sentence 1) and is yellow (sentence 4), it can be logically inferred that greg, being of the same species as julius, is also likely to be yellow. this is the most reasonable assumption based on the provided information, as there is no other color mentioned in relation to frogs.
